### `01` · Automated Valuation Environment Architect

> *Eliminating 1,000 hours of manual file management annually across a 40-person actuarial hub*

![Python](https://img.shields.io/badge/Python-3776AB?style=flat-square&logo=python&logoColor=white)
![Streamlit](https://img.shields.io/badge/Streamlit-FF4B4B?style=flat-square&logo=streamlit&logoColor=white)
![Pandas](https://img.shields.io/badge/Pandas-150458?style=flat-square&logo=pandas&logoColor=white)

Every pension valuation cycle, 40 analysts manually copied, renamed, and organized 50 template files per client — a process consuming **500+ hours annually** before any actual analysis began. This engine eliminates it entirely.

15 clients × 50 files × 1 min per file
= 750 minutes per analyst per cycle
= 12.5 hours per analyst

× 40 analysts
= 500 hours per cycle
```
Input:  clients.xlsx  +  2026_templates/
                              ↓
        Reads client list · finds templates · builds filenames
        Enforces naming convention · routes to correct subfolders
                              ↓
Output: 0231_Marathon_Petroleum_2026_Gain_Loss_v01.xlsx
        → clients/0231_Marathon_Petroleum/Gain_Loss/  ✓
```

| Metric | Value |
|--------|-------|
| Files processed per run | 750+ |
| Processing time | < 2 seconds |
| Manual time replaced | **500 hrs/year** |
| Naming error rate | 0% |

